Michigan won't have any evictions until May 15, under a new order Gov.
â€œRight now the most effective tool we have to fight this virus is to stay home and slow the spread through person to person contact," Whitmer said in a press release.
"That is why it is important to extend my executive order to suspend evictions so people can focus on staying home and staying safe."
Landlords report that the ban has discouraged many from paying and that more help is needed to avoid a foreclosure crisis.
The federal CARES Act, the $2.2 trillion economic rescue package, halts evictions for properties with federally backed mortgages for 120 days.